<br>
I am hosting an event for the first 16 Knights that hail me tonight (10/28/2002) in Freeport. I will be at the West Gate announcing the event at around 7:30pm EST. The event will begin at 8pm EST<br>
<br>
Details are as follows: <br>
Myself, an experienced Knight, do hereby announce an event to train and equip a group of 16 young Knights of levels 9 through 14. The event will consist of a mass arena duel of the sixteen. The winner is the one left standing. All pre-existing buffs will be dispelled before entering the arena. Participants are free to use their own magics, but may not be assisted by any outside friends.<br>
<br>
My wife, Brishen, will award prizes to Knights as they fall and will be available to bind participants outside the arena if they so desire.<br>
<br>
I will be judging the event and reserve complete control over the organization of the event.<br>
<br>
Every participant will receive a gift for attending. I have hand selected the gifts as appropriate for the Paladin class and all are nice items that would be very difficult to attain at this level range. There are no special pre-requisites or fees to join the event. <br>
<br>
The winner of the event will receive the following grand victor's prize which includes:<br>
<br>
1. 100pp in coin<br>
2. A complete, visible suit of Fine Plate armor forged by me<br>
3. A Velium Round Shield<br>
4. A Sporali Defender's Blade or Crystalline Blade (choice of winner)<br>
<br>
All other participants will receive a gift for attendance. I have various nice pieces of armor, weapons, shields and other misc items that will be distributed to participants.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, this event is limited to 16 participants.<br>
Do not sign up here, simply find and hail me after I announce the event tonight in West Freeport at the gate. First 16 to hail me are automatically entered into the contest. Erudite, High Elven, and Human Paladins of the appropriate level range are all welcome, Freeport need not be your starting city. If the event goes well, I will repeat it at a future date in Qeynos.<br>
<br>
Spectators are of course quite welcome to attend, but any active particpation is prohibited, so please be there to observe only.<br>
<br>
With Honor<br>
Teodoric Luminae<br>
Knight of the 51st circle<br>
